# What is REST API?

REST stands for **Representational State Transfer**.

A REST API is an API that follows REST architectural principles and communicates using HTTP.

Examples

GET /students

POST /students

PUT /students/5

PATCH /students/5

DELETE /students/5

---

# REST Principles (Important for Freshers)

## 1. Client-Server

Client and Server are independent.

---

## 2. Stateless

The server does not remember previous requests.

Every request is treated as a new request.

---

## 3. Uniform Interface

API endpoints should follow a consistent naming convention.

Correct

/students

/courses

/teachers

Wrong

/getStudents

/createStudent

---

## 4. Resource-Based URLs

REST APIs use nouns instead of verbs.

Correct

/students

Wrong

/getStudents

